TodayÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s armored-up policemen are a far cry from the constables of early America. The unrest of the 1960s brought about the invention of the SWAT unitÃ¢â‚¬â€which in turn led to the debut of military tactics in the ranks of police officers. NixonÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s War on Drugs, ReaganÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s War on Poverty, ClintonÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s COPS program, the postÃ¢â‚¬â€œ9/11 security state under Bush and Obama: by degrees, each of these innovations expanded and empowered police forces, always at the expense of civil liberties. And these are just four among a slew of reckless programs.

